2.1.3 Troubleshooting
---------------------

If ‘ldapsearch’ exits with an error, you’ll see a message like this in
the ‘*Messages*’ buffer (all on one line):

     ldap-search-internal: Failed ldapsearch invocation:
        ldapsearch "-Hldaps://ldap.gnu.org" "-bou=people,dc=gnu,dc=org"
        "-Dgnu\emacsuser" "-W" "-LL" "-tt" "(&(mail=name*))"
        "givenname" "sn" "mail"

   The ‘ldapsearch’ command is formatted such that it can be copied and
pasted into a terminal.  Set the ‘ldapsearch’ debug level to 5 by
appending ‘-d 5’ to the command line.


